Purpresture.definition: wrongful appropriation of land subject to the rights of others
Purpresture.origin: [Anglo-French, alteration of Old French porpresure , from porprendre to seize, occupy, enclose, from por- for + prendre to take, from Latin prehendere ]

1.1: wrongful appropriation of land subject to the rights of others

2.1: an encroachment upon or enclosure of real property (as highways, sidewalks, or harbors) subject to common or public rights
